# Architecture Rules

The system has three modules with a strict, one-directional dependency flow:

```
ui  ──commands──▶  simulation  ──snapshots──▶  render
                       │
                       └── only PlanckAdapter imports `planck`
```

## The boundary law

- `src/simulation/**` MUST NOT import:
  - `react`, `react-dom`, any React hooks
  - `pixi.js`
  - `src/render/**`, `src/ui/**`
  - browser globals (`window`, `document`, `navigator`, `localStorage`, `requestAnimationFrame`)
- Only `src/simulation/adapters/PlanckAdapter.ts` may import `planck`. Nothing else in the codebase imports `planck`.
- `src/render/**` MUST NOT import from `src/ui/**` or call into Planck. It consumes immutable `Snapshot` objects from the simulation.
- `src/ui/**` interacts with simulation **only** via the `World` public API exposed through `useSimulation`. UI never mutates physics state directly.
- `Snapshot` and `BodyView` returned by the kernel are read-only. In dev they are `Object.freeze`d.

## Adding a new entity type

Anything the simulation can spawn — a body or a connector — must also be reachable from the UI. If it isn't in the toolbar, it doesn't exist for users, and the welcome scene becomes a museum of things they can't build.

### New body type (Ball / Box / Magnet …)

In order:

1. A factory in `src/simulation/mechanics/<type>.ts` returning a normalized `BodySpec`.
2. Snapshot fields in `src/simulation/core/types.ts` if needed.
3. A view in `src/render/scene/BodyView.ts`.
4. A toolbar entry in `src/ui/panels/Toolbar.tsx` (icon, label, `Tool` id) plus spawn handling in `src/ui/canvas/usePointerGestures.ts`.

### New connector type (Rope / Hinge / Spring …)

In order:

1. A factory in `src/simulation/mechanics/<type>.ts` returning a normalized `ConstraintSpec`.
2. Snapshot fields in `src/simulation/core/types.ts` if the connector needs to be drawn.
3. A view in `src/render/scene/ConstraintView.ts`.
4. A toolbar entry in `src/ui/panels/Toolbar.tsx` plus the multi-anchor placement gesture in `src/ui/canvas/usePointerGestures.ts`.

### Toolbar step is the user contract

Step 4 (toolbar + gesture wiring) is **strongly recommended** for every new entity type. The kernel and the welcome scene must not gain abilities the user can't reproduce on an empty canvas.

It can be deferred — but only with an explicit note in the commit message saying why and when it will follow, and never across a milestone boundary.

No cross-cutting edits. Each step lives in its own commit per `04-workflow.mdc`.

## Determinism

Same initial spec + same command stream + same `dt` ⇒ identical tick-by-tick snapshots. EM forces are inserted in stable id order. Any change that breaks determinism requires an explicit note.

## What goes where

| Concern | Module |
|---|---|
| Body shapes, masses, joints | `simulation/mechanics` |
| Forces (Coulomb, Lorentz, dipole) | `simulation/electromagnetism` |
| Time, stepping, snapshots | `simulation/core` |
| Wrap Planck.js | `simulation/adapters` |
| Initial scene factories | `simulation/scenes` |
| Pixi scene graph, camera | `render` |
| Buttons, panels, hooks, store | `ui` |
